  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong>&nbsp;(skins on) roughly into bite-size&nbsp;pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook over a high heat for 15 min or until fork-tender</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and leave them to steam-dry&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim and slice the <strong>spring onion</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel the skin off the <strong>smoked&nbsp;</strong><strong>mackerel</strong>&nbsp;and discard</p>\r\n<p>Flake the flesh into bite-sized pieces</p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>chilli jam</strong> and a splash of &nbsp;<strong>cold water</strong> in a small bowl - this is your <strong>sweet chilli dressing&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Re-boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Shred the <strong>little gem lettuce</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the&nbsp;<strong>sugar snaps</strong>&nbsp;in half length-ways</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>potatoes</strong> are drained, transfer them to a large bowl &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Break the <strong>noodle nest</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> in half&nbsp;over&nbsp;the empty pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p>\r\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-7 min until tender with a slight bite, then drain and run under<strong> cold water</strong> until they're cooled&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, mash the drained&nbsp;<strong>potatoes</strong> with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>sliced&nbsp;spring onion</strong>, <strong>flaked mackerel</strong> and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour&nbsp;</strong>and season generously with both&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then mix to combine to a dough</p>\r\n<p>Divide the dough into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span>&nbsp;pieces and roll each into a golf ball</p>\r\n<p>Pat each ball down - these are your <strong>mackerel fishcakes&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick)&nbsp;with a very large drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> (you need enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;hot, add the <strong>mackerel</strong>&nbsp;<strong>fishcakes</strong> and cook for 4 min on both sides or until they're browned</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>fishcakes</strong> to<strong> kitchen paper</strong> to soak up any excess oil and sprinkle them with <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained noodles</strong>, <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> and <strong>sliced sugar snaps</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>sweet chilli dressing</strong> and give everything a good mix up - this is your <strong>noodle salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/881.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>m</strong><strong>ackerel fishcakes</strong>&nbsp;with the&nbsp;<strong>noodle salad</strong> and sprinkle with the <strong>toasted</strong>&nbsp;<strong>sesame seeds</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
